        public void setAuthToken​(byte[] authToken)

        Manually sets the authToken. This should only be done in special cases such as when restoring an Approval from the database. Note: Setting this to AdminInformation.getRandomToken() means that this object is treated as it were created internal in EJBCA. Do not do that unless trusting the object!
